page.title: 13A WALK IN THE NEW FOREST
page.content: In July we went for a walk to Beaulieu and part of the New Forest.When we got to Beaulieu we found a nice place to sit .When we were all sitting down we got out our traffic census out and started working on them.My traffic census was to do with the colours of the cars that went by.The most popular colour was white.After we did our traffic census we went to have lunch. After lunch we went for our long walk. On the way we found lots of interesting things like ants nests so we put a stick on one of their paths to see if the ant would find its way over it and the ant did. When we got back to school every one was tired so we all had a little rest from doing work. Our teacher asked us if we had enjoyed the day out and everyone said yes.
